{
  "stem": "4693.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Among the people in the camp was a Pole who was president of the National Legal Association of Poland, member of the Polish senate, president of Rosenheim, was one of the biggest cities of this, professor of philosophy of law, member of the Committee of Five.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "He was running big Polish anti-Semitic party, National Democratic Party.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And this guy was old, he was around 60.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When we were coming from work, he was always coming to my bed and talking to me.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I said to him on one day, I said to him why do you-- you have so many Poles here, why do you come to me.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You are-- you are leading the anti-Semitic party in Poland.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he said, look, what do I have common with them?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I can't talk with them--I can talk with you.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was-- he study at a very high level.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had very-- I don't want to repeat our discussions about situation of Jews, about his position and everything.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] On the 22nd of June, 1941, Germans attack Russia.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A few weeks earlier, at once came instruction that all the political prisoners who are on the special jobs have to go on ordinary jobs, because they can't be trusted.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was taken away from hospital and sent to work.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But, this time, I had already connections.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So also I was sent to work as a laborer outside where they were building houses for the future workers of this refinery.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was put in charge-- illegal, not legally, but practically-- for receiving material which are delivered from the harbor, building materials.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This materials were delivered by Russians who were forcibly sent over there but who were not inmates of the camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
